03:19.264 --> 03:21.362
hey. Harry.
Yo.

03:21.497 --> 03:23.328
You, uh, you in a hurry?

03:23.495 --> 03:25.226
Having lunch with billets.

03:25.326 --> 03:27.524
Edgar and I are going down to
palm Springs to do an interview.

03:27.624 --> 03:30.089
You guys get all
the boondoggles.

03:30.188 --> 03:31.253
Let me talk to you.

03:31.353 --> 03:32.720
Yeah.

03:34.251 --> 03:36.149
I need the room.

03:39.246 --> 03:42.544
[ Door opens, closes ]

03:42.643 --> 03:44.176
Am I in trouble?

03:44.275 --> 03:46.774
[ Chuckles ] No.

03:46.873 --> 03:49.037
The deputy chief's son,
George?

03:49.137 --> 03:50.470
Not a bad cop, what I hear.

03:50.570 --> 03:51.869
Yeah, well, he can stray

03:51.969 --> 03:53.233
off the reservation
from time to time.

03:53.333 --> 03:55.466
And...?

03:55.499 --> 03:57.697
And when officer Pierce
and Irving junior

03:57.796 --> 03:59.728
pulled over
this waits character,

03:59.828 --> 04:01.726
apparently Irving
deliberately

04:01.826 --> 04:03.924
punched in the wrong
plate number

04:04.023 --> 04:05.889
because he wanted
to search the Van.

04:05.989 --> 04:07.621
Guess he reversed a couple
of numbers.

04:07.720 --> 04:09.619
An old-school move.
[ Chuckling ] I know.

04:09.719 --> 04:11.584
Did it myself a couple times
back in the day.

04:11.684 --> 04:13.182
But the thing is, Harry,
a case like this,

04:13.282 --> 04:15.847
you do not want a hinky probable
cause on the Van search.

04:15.947 --> 04:17.811
So, tell Pierce
to keep his mouth shut.

04:17.911 --> 04:20.242
Yeah, well, that's where the
rubber hits the fucking road,

04:20.342 --> 04:21.941
my friend, because
apparently this Pierce

04:22.041 --> 04:24.672
is some kind of eagle scout,
wants me to file a complaint.

04:24.772 --> 04:26.703
Goes to paper,
it fucks the case.

04:26.803 --> 04:29.267
Yeah. And me.
You ever go camping,

04:29.435 --> 04:31.066
accidentally wipe your ass
with poison oak?

04:33.097 --> 04:34.130
Okay. So, no.

04:34.230 --> 04:35.795
But if I write junior up,

04:35.894 --> 04:39.325
Irving's the camper
and I'm the poison oak.

04:39.426 --> 04:41.689
Not only that,
if I don't file,

04:41.789 --> 04:44.487
then all of a sudden I've got
a failure-to-take-action gripe

04:44.587 --> 04:46.485
coming at me
from officer Pierce.

04:46.585 --> 04:47.850
It's fucking
department politics.

04:47.950 --> 04:49.782
Don't worry about it.
I'll talk to Pierce.

04:49.882 --> 04:51.280
You will?

04:51.415 --> 04:53.078
Thanks, Harry.
I owe you.

04:53.178 --> 04:55.810
Nice analogy.

04:55.910 --> 04:57.675
[ Chuckles ]

05:00.606 --> 05:02.037
Kind of a hike
to palm Springs.

05:02.137 --> 05:05.134
Why don't you just call her,
tell her her son's dead?

05:05.234 --> 05:06.933
I want to look her
in the eyes.

05:08.864 --> 05:10.929
[ Singsong voice ]
Edgar's gonna want to
stop at the outlets.

05:11.029 --> 05:12.428
[ Chuckles ]

05:12.528 --> 05:13.494
Got to hand it to him.
He always looks correct.

05:13.594 --> 05:15.025
He's a clothes horse.

05:15.125 --> 05:16.458
He's got more shoes
than you do.

05:18.390 --> 05:20.953
You holding up okay,
Harry?

05:21.053 --> 05:23.251
Ask your questions.

05:23.385 --> 05:26.482
Arthur's mom
was absent, too.

05:26.582 --> 05:28.381
I'm curious about her.

05:28.414 --> 05:30.545
If she hadn't abandoned
the kids,

05:30.644 --> 05:32.942
maybe the boy would
still be alive. Who knows?

05:33.042 --> 05:35.507
Well...Just don't make

05:35.607 --> 05:38.936
the delacroix murder
too personal, okay?

05:39.036 --> 05:40.436
It is personal.

05:40.535 --> 05:42.767
I'd be lying if I told you
any different.

05:42.867 --> 05:43.966
That's how I work.

05:44.066 --> 05:46.896
You talk
to your kid recently?

05:46.996 --> 05:48.695
Supposed to talk tonight.

05:48.795 --> 05:50.893
She calls me Harry.

05:50.992 --> 05:52.558
[ Laughs ]

05:52.658 --> 05:55.955
It's just a phase.
I wouldn't worry about it.

05:57.886 --> 05:59.784
Any word from downtown?

05:59.884 --> 06:01.116
Belk called.

06:01.216 --> 06:02.382
They're gonna read
the verdict

06:02.482 --> 06:03.714
first thing
tomorrow morning.

06:03.814 --> 06:04.847
Mm.

06:13.572 --> 06:14.738
Finish your lunch, Harry.

06:14.838 --> 06:16.636
You've got a long drive
ahead of you.

06:23.730 --> 06:26.493
When we get down near cabazon,
pull off on exit 104.

06:26.593 --> 06:28.225
I want to stop
at the outlets.

06:28.326 --> 06:30.324
I knew it.

06:30.390 --> 06:32.721
It's not like
it's out of the way.

06:32.821 --> 06:33.920
We got work to do.

06:34.020 --> 06:35.685
I want to get
something new.

06:35.784 --> 06:38.216
Man's got to dress a certain
way when he's on the job.

06:38.317 --> 06:39.481
You're obsessed
with clothing.

06:39.581 --> 06:40.780
You're like a chick, man.

06:40.880 --> 06:42.612
An ugly chick, but a chick.
[ Chuckles ]

06:42.712 --> 06:44.511
See, I can't expect
an off-the-rack,

06:44.610 --> 06:46.774
men's wearhouse motherfucker
like you to understand.

06:46.874 --> 06:48.772
I'm not stopping.

06:48.872 --> 06:50.471
Please.

06:50.571 --> 06:52.503
I'll buy you a pack of
those bubblegum cigarettes

06:52.603 --> 06:54.067
on account
you don't smoke no more.

06:54.167 --> 06:55.534
Still not stopping.

07:07.356 --> 07:08.888
Make it fast, shoedog.

07:08.988 --> 07:10.353
I know just what I want.

07:10.453 --> 07:11.951
A pair of double-buck
monk straps in tan

07:12.051 --> 07:13.584
with a wingtip detailing
on the vamp.

07:13.684 --> 07:17.080
I got wingtips. They're brown.
No vamp, though.

07:17.180 --> 07:19.279
I'm not talking about those
florsheim clodhoppers you wear.

07:19.345 --> 07:21.277
These shoes
are called the burns.

07:21.377 --> 07:22.741
Made in Italy
by to boot New York.

07:22.841 --> 07:24.007
Let me ask you something.

07:24.107 --> 07:25.473
If they're made in Italy,

07:25.573 --> 07:27.771
why is the company called
to boot New York?

07:27.871 --> 07:28.836
For real?

07:28.935 --> 07:29.902
I'm just saying.

07:44.289 --> 07:45.820
Hey.
You guys on the clock?

07:45.920 --> 07:50.016
Here to see Christine waters,
312 deep waters drive.

07:50.116 --> 07:51.715
And will she know
what this is about?

07:51.815 --> 07:53.248
Not unless she's psychic.

07:53.281 --> 07:56.278
Hold on.

07:56.378 --> 07:58.243
Deep waters drive?
In the desert?

07:58.343 --> 08:00.307
Second husband
was Ralph waters.

08:00.407 --> 08:01.506
He built this development.

08:01.606 --> 08:03.404
She landed
in the high cotton.

08:03.504 --> 08:05.069
Bailed on her first family,
ends up here?

08:05.237 --> 08:06.535
Ain't it the truth?

08:06.635 --> 08:08.633
Mrs. waters wants to know
what this is about.

08:08.733 --> 08:10.997
We'll discuss it privately
with her.

08:11.097 --> 08:13.761
We have a court order.
Open the gate.

08:17.691 --> 08:19.224
[ Buzzer ]

08:19.324 --> 08:21.721
You know, that tough-guy routine
might work okay in L.A.

08:21.821 --> 08:23.120
But out here in the desert,

08:23.220 --> 08:25.484
we like to do things a...
A little differently.

08:52.227 --> 08:53.592
Mrs. waters, please.

08:57.255 --> 08:59.752
Eugene said you had
a court order.

08:59.852 --> 09:01.418
May I see it, detective?

09:01.518 --> 09:04.815
He must have misunderstood.
I said we could get one.

09:04.914 --> 09:07.012
[ Sighs ]
Well, you're here now.

09:07.180 --> 09:09.411
Let's get this over with,
whatever this is.

09:09.511 --> 09:10.876
It's about your son,
Mrs. waters.

09:10.976 --> 09:13.274
Arthur.
How do you know about --

09:13.374 --> 09:15.738
he's dead.
He was murdered.

09:19.534 --> 09:21.799
Oh, my god.

09:21.899 --> 09:24.164
Please, sit down.

09:24.197 --> 09:25.596
[ Sighs ]

09:33.588 --> 09:35.819
Have you been in contact
with him?

09:35.919 --> 09:37.418
No.

09:37.518 --> 09:38.617
No.

09:38.717 --> 09:41.315
I lost touch with him
a long time ago.

09:41.414 --> 09:43.712
His remains were recently
found up on Laurel canyon.

09:43.812 --> 09:46.144
We identified him
through his medical records.

09:46.244 --> 09:48.575
Wh--when did -- okay.

09:48.674 --> 09:50.839
He would have been...

09:50.939 --> 09:53.138
32 last August.

09:53.171 --> 09:54.137
Send him a card?

09:54.170 --> 09:56.900
Excuse me?

09:56.999 --> 09:59.032
Oh. Right.
You'd lost touch.

09:59.132 --> 10:01.829
Your daughter said he
disappeared 20 years ago.

10:01.929 --> 10:03.761
I didn't know.

10:03.860 --> 10:06.292
We believe he was murdered
shortly after he disappeared.

10:06.391 --> 10:07.924
Oh, god.

10:08.023 --> 10:09.788
All these years,
no contact with your family?

10:09.888 --> 10:11.686
No.

10:11.786 --> 10:13.052
Nothing at all?

10:14.618 --> 10:18.714
[ Sighs ]
About a year after I left,

10:18.814 --> 10:22.843
I drove by the house one night
to check on the children,

10:22.943 --> 10:27.006
hoping to get a glimpse of them,
make sure they were okay.

10:27.107 --> 10:30.036
But the drapes were drawn
and...I didn't stop.

10:30.137 --> 10:31.035
Well, why not?

10:31.136 --> 10:32.567
I was afraid

10:32.667 --> 10:36.464
of what my ex-husband
would do if he saw me.

10:36.564 --> 10:37.896
When you filed for divorce,
you cited physical abuse.

10:37.996 --> 10:39.661
Sam beat me.

10:39.760 --> 10:40.926
I ran away.

10:41.026 --> 10:42.792
I thought
that the children

10:42.891 --> 10:45.090
would be better off
without me.

10:45.190 --> 10:48.287
Better off?
With an abusive alcoholic?

10:53.881 --> 10:55.081
[ Sighs ]

10:55.181 --> 10:56.845
I'd like you to leave now,

10:56.944 --> 10:58.543
both of you.

10:58.643 --> 11:00.941
If there's anything further,
you can contact my attorney.

11:01.076 --> 11:03.074
Give us a moment, Jerry?

11:03.174 --> 11:04.505
[ Sighs ]
I want you to go, too.

11:06.935 --> 11:08.668
[ Sighs ]

11:08.768 --> 11:11.698
Mrs. waters, you do want us to
try and find your son's killer?

11:11.798 --> 11:12.730
Of course.

11:21.057 --> 11:24.055
[ Exhales sharply ]

11:24.120 --> 11:27.651
I-i gave this to Artie.

11:27.750 --> 11:30.182
Where did you find it?

11:30.282 --> 11:31.713
It was recovered
from the gravesite.

11:31.813 --> 11:33.511
Do you remember
where you bought it?

11:33.611 --> 11:36.243
Uh...

11:36.343 --> 11:39.939
No, i-i probably
picked it up somewhere.

11:40.040 --> 11:41.471
A yard sale, maybe?

11:41.571 --> 11:44.102
Mrs. waters, did you
ever see your husband,

11:44.202 --> 11:46.467
your -- your ex-husband
strike the children?

11:46.566 --> 11:50.695
No, I was his punching bag,
detective.

11:50.795 --> 11:52.760
Just me.

11:52.860 --> 11:55.126
Why? Do you think
Sam killed Arthur?

11:55.226 --> 11:57.024
We don't know
who killed your son.

11:57.124 --> 12:00.254
We're still in the very early
stages of our investigation.

12:00.354 --> 12:02.385
What about
funeral arrangements?

12:02.485 --> 12:04.450
I mean,
i suppose I should --

12:04.550 --> 12:06.914
well, you could
contact the coroner.
Yeah.

12:07.015 --> 12:08.546
Or you could call
your daughter.

12:10.544 --> 12:13.075
Sheila?

12:13.175 --> 12:15.507
What does she look like?

12:15.607 --> 12:16.838
Like you.

12:17.006 --> 12:20.568
A little taller, maybe.

12:20.668 --> 12:22.733
Does she have
a family, or --

12:22.833 --> 12:24.165
not that I'm aware of.

12:24.265 --> 12:26.662
She's still
in the same house.

12:26.762 --> 12:29.128
She is?

12:29.227 --> 12:30.825
She stayed there...

12:30.993 --> 12:33.556
In case
your son ever came home.

12:49.976 --> 12:51.407
The bitch
got under my skin.

12:51.507 --> 12:54.371
You know how she talked about
driving by her old house,

12:54.471 --> 12:56.602
trying to get a glimpse
of her kids

12:56.702 --> 12:58.600
through the windows
at night?

12:58.700 --> 13:01.031
I do that.

13:01.131 --> 13:03.030
More than I care to say.

13:03.129 --> 13:07.226
I had everything, man.
I didn't know it.

13:07.325 --> 13:10.956
I fucked up, screwed around,
other women.

13:11.056 --> 13:14.319
I was weak like that.
[ Sighs ]

13:14.419 --> 13:17.849
Now I find myself outside
my own damn house at night,

13:17.950 --> 13:19.948
looking at my kids
through glass.

13:19.981 --> 13:21.347
But you know what?

13:21.446 --> 13:24.576
Wrong as I was,
I'm still in their lives.

13:24.676 --> 13:25.943
This woman in there,

13:26.009 --> 13:27.407
she just gave up
and walked away.

13:27.507 --> 13:30.538
Said she never saw the husband
hit the kids.

13:30.638 --> 13:32.802
You think he started beating
Arthur after she left?

13:32.936 --> 13:34.534
I do.

13:34.634 --> 13:37.764
I bet that's exactly what
she's thinking right now.

13:37.932 --> 13:39.596
Christine waters lived
a different kind of hell.

13:39.695 --> 13:41.394
She's still in it.

13:47.089 --> 13:48.587
Officer Pierce.

13:48.687 --> 13:49.954
Sir.

13:50.053 --> 13:51.452
Second for me?

13:51.552 --> 13:52.551
What's up?

13:54.416 --> 13:55.581
It's rondell, right?

13:55.681 --> 13:56.914
I go by Ron.

13:57.014 --> 13:59.045
So, Ron, this beef
with your partner --

13:59.145 --> 14:01.476
guy's a cowboy.
I beef him, I'm fucked.

14:01.575 --> 14:02.808
I don't, I'm fucked.

14:02.909 --> 14:04.307
So, if I'm gonna
end up fucked,

14:04.407 --> 14:06.238
I'm gonna get fucked
doing the right thing.

14:06.338 --> 14:08.204
And you can tell that
to the deputy chief.

14:08.303 --> 14:10.268
I'm not here 'cause of Irving
or his son.

14:10.368 --> 14:12.300
Then why?
Look.

14:12.400 --> 14:14.498
Your complaint goes to paper,
it becomes official record.

14:14.597 --> 14:16.162
Waits gets kicked loose.

14:16.262 --> 14:17.727
The judge has no choice because
you've made it official

14:17.895 --> 14:19.559
that the probable cause
on the stop was tricked.

14:19.659 --> 14:20.592
You want that?

14:20.692 --> 14:21.991
No, man.

14:22.091 --> 14:23.489
That's definitely not
what I want.

14:23.589 --> 14:25.553
Right. 'Cause you saw in
the back of the Van, right,

14:25.653 --> 14:27.585
what waits did?
Yeah. I saw.

14:27.685 --> 14:29.018
Okay.
So, you got a problem.

14:29.118 --> 14:30.616
There's ways to solve it

14:30.715 --> 14:32.514
in-house without compromising
the case.

14:32.614 --> 14:34.080
So, what do I do?

14:34.180 --> 14:36.543
I got to protect myself.

14:36.643 --> 14:38.276
This job's all I got,

14:38.376 --> 14:40.340
and I don't have a deputy chief
daddy watching my six.

14:40.440 --> 14:42.605
Yeah. How about
i talk to mankiewicz,
get you a new partner?

14:42.704 --> 14:44.037
Squared-away cat
like yourself?

14:44.137 --> 14:45.935
I don't know,
the others figure

14:46.035 --> 14:48.666
I bitched out George,
treat me like a leper.

14:48.766 --> 14:50.764
Mank will handle it.
You two made the big bust.

14:50.865 --> 14:53.295
Time to separate you,
spread out the street smarts.

14:58.590 --> 15:01.520
That might work.

15:01.620 --> 15:03.086
I got this.

15:09.413 --> 15:11.346
Hey.

15:11.445 --> 15:12.845
Hey.

15:12.944 --> 15:14.843
I was just about to change
into my civvies.

15:14.909 --> 15:16.407
Feel like
grabbing a bite?

15:16.507 --> 15:19.404
We could squeeze into one of
those booths at Dan tana's.

15:19.504 --> 15:20.737
I'd like to.

15:20.837 --> 15:22.269
I just got back
from a road trip.

15:22.368 --> 15:23.835
Shitloads of paperwork.

15:23.934 --> 15:25.866
I've got to return calls.
I can wait.

15:25.966 --> 15:29.362
Thing is, I promised my
daughter I'd call her tonight.

15:29.462 --> 15:31.260
Rain check?

15:31.360 --> 15:32.659
Yeah, sure.

15:32.826 --> 15:33.991
Is everything okay?

15:34.091 --> 15:36.156
Yeah, fine.
It's the case.

15:36.256 --> 15:38.387
I'm just a little distracted,
you know?
Yeah.

15:38.486 --> 15:39.652
Maybe tomorrow?

15:39.820 --> 15:41.451
Cool. Call me.

15:47.712 --> 15:49.443
[ Laughs ] What?

15:49.543 --> 15:50.876
I know that look.

15:50.976 --> 15:52.341
Yeah, if anyone would...

15:52.441 --> 15:54.406
Mm.

16:15.652 --> 16:17.985
[ Dialing ]

16:20.782 --> 16:21.781
[ Ringing ]

16:21.881 --> 16:23.080
Eleanor: Hello?

16:23.180 --> 16:24.079
Hey, it's Harry.

16:24.179 --> 16:26.310
Harry.
Has there been a verdict?

16:26.410 --> 16:27.675
Tomorrow.
Good luck.

16:27.776 --> 16:29.507
Thanks.

16:29.606 --> 16:31.872
It was horrible,
bringing up your mom.

16:31.972 --> 16:33.603
It's all over
the Internet.

16:33.770 --> 16:35.302
Yeah.
What are you gonna do?

16:35.401 --> 16:36.334
Is she there?

16:36.433 --> 16:37.666
Yeah. Hold on.

16:37.767 --> 16:39.265
Maddie,
your dad's on the phone!

16:39.365 --> 16:40.629
You just caught us.

16:40.764 --> 16:41.763
We're on our way out
to soccer practice.

16:41.796 --> 16:43.427
Here she is.

16:43.527 --> 16:44.760
Hey, maddie.

16:44.793 --> 16:46.491
Hey, Harry.

16:46.591 --> 16:47.890
Soccer practice at night?

16:47.990 --> 16:49.921
Yeah.
Too hot during the day.

16:50.021 --> 16:52.753
Plus, skin cancer.
Hello.

16:52.786 --> 16:54.751
[ Chuckles ]
Good point.

16:54.817 --> 16:55.850
Are you coming
for Christmas?

16:55.950 --> 16:58.313
I'm working on it.

16:58.413 --> 17:01.610
Hope so.
Well, I should go.

17:01.745 --> 17:03.409
Coach makes us run laps
if we're late.

17:03.508 --> 17:04.574
Is everything okay?

17:04.742 --> 17:06.340
Getting used to Vegas?

17:06.440 --> 17:08.072
Yeah.
Vegas is okay.

17:08.171 --> 17:10.302
Kind of bright and shiny,
you know?

17:10.402 --> 17:11.736
Put on your shades.

17:11.835 --> 17:13.734
I'll talk to you
in a couple days. Good?

17:13.767 --> 17:15.631
Okay.
Bye, Harry.

17:15.732 --> 17:17.163
I love y--

17:17.263 --> 17:19.029
[ click ]

17:20.860 --> 17:22.958
[ Phone beeps ]

17:24.523 --> 17:26.055
[ Phone thuds ]

17:42.807 --> 17:47.236
[ Bell jingling ]

17:47.335 --> 17:48.268
Have a good one.

17:48.367 --> 17:50.700
Thank you.

17:50.800 --> 17:53.830
Has the jury
reached a verdict?

17:53.930 --> 17:55.695
Yes, we have, your honor.

18:07.684 --> 18:09.982
We, the jury,
duly empanelled

18:10.082 --> 18:11.980
and sworn in the case
of Rosa flores

18:12.080 --> 18:15.210
versus hieronymus bosch
and the city of Los Angeles,

18:15.310 --> 18:19.673
upon our oaths do find in favor
of plaintiff Rosa flores.

18:19.706 --> 18:21.672
[ Gavel bangs ]

18:21.737 --> 18:23.469
We find full damages to be $1.

18:23.569 --> 18:25.768
Judge: Ladies and gentlemen
of the jury,

18:25.867 --> 18:27.531
thank you for your service.

18:27.666 --> 18:29.563
What did she say?
A dollar?

18:29.664 --> 18:31.828
That's some bullshit.
I was right as rain
with that shooting.

18:31.928 --> 18:33.960
Oh, come on.
Take yes for an answer, Harry.

18:34.060 --> 18:36.658
Will ya?
The jury's made a statement.

18:36.724 --> 18:38.122
Yeah, that I fucked up.

18:38.222 --> 18:40.420
No, that you got a bad guy
off the street,

18:40.519 --> 18:42.452
you just bent the rules
a little too far.

18:42.551 --> 18:45.650
Well, I can appeal
if you want me to.

18:45.682 --> 18:49.378
Come on. You're not serious.
You wouldn't.

18:49.478 --> 18:51.110
It was a rhetorical
suggestion, Harry.

18:51.210 --> 18:53.308
Harry.

19:03.666 --> 19:06.630
Feeling good about yourself,
counselor?

19:06.696 --> 19:08.194
Just another day
at the office.

19:08.294 --> 19:09.628
You seem pretty pleased

19:09.693 --> 19:11.525
for someone who just won
her client a dollar.

19:11.626 --> 19:12.890
What's your cut --
33 1/3 cents?

19:12.990 --> 19:15.722
I did a little better
than that, detective.

19:15.822 --> 19:17.420
The plaintiff won,

19:17.519 --> 19:19.984
so I'm not limited to my
piece of her dollar.

19:20.083 --> 19:21.382
No?
No.

19:21.482 --> 19:22.848
Mrs. flores won't be
paying my legal fees.

19:22.948 --> 19:26.012
That obligation will fall
to the city of Los Angeles.

19:26.112 --> 19:27.611
How much?

19:27.644 --> 19:30.141
Ballpark, I'll probably
bill them $550,000.

19:30.241 --> 19:31.707
Good luck with that.

19:31.807 --> 19:33.671
Oh, they'll squawk,
go through the motions.

19:33.771 --> 19:36.703
Little do-si-do around the
dance floor a couple of times,

19:36.802 --> 19:38.601
do the ritual
back-and-forth.

19:38.634 --> 19:42.030
And then we'll settle
at $250,000, $275,000?

19:42.130 --> 19:43.896
So they call you money.

19:43.996 --> 19:44.728
That, they do.

19:44.828 --> 19:46.459
See you around, detective.

19:46.594 --> 19:48.791
Most likely in court.

19:48.891 --> 19:52.420
Guys like you never stop
stepping on their own dicks.

19:52.588 --> 19:54.919
[ Car door slams ]

20:04.810 --> 20:07.140
You must be relieved.

20:07.240 --> 20:09.238
Could have been worse.

20:09.338 --> 20:10.737
Let's walk the river.

20:12.070 --> 20:14.467
They've done a good job
down here.

20:14.568 --> 20:15.899
Long way to go,

20:15.999 --> 20:17.698
but not the absolute joke
it used to be.

20:17.798 --> 20:20.529
Still a giant
concrete gutter.

20:20.628 --> 20:22.627
Cities need gutters,
bosch.

20:24.958 --> 20:27.421
The district attorney's
authorized a field trip

20:27.522 --> 20:29.620
for raynard waits,
tomorrow.

20:29.720 --> 20:30.786
Why would he do that?

20:30.886 --> 20:33.750
Photo op, publicity stunt,

20:33.850 --> 20:35.748
to jump-start
his mayoral campaign.

20:35.848 --> 20:37.479
You were gonna convince him

20:37.580 --> 20:40.077
waits lied about killing
Arthur delacroix.

20:40.177 --> 20:41.343
Waits is lying.

20:41.442 --> 20:43.507
Attention is his m.O.

20:43.607 --> 20:46.704
He wants the spotlight
as much as o'shea does.

20:46.804 --> 20:48.469
This field trip makes him king
for a day.

20:48.570 --> 20:51.734
Well, he's convinced o'shea.

20:51.833 --> 20:53.798
Send some people up there
with gas probes.

20:53.898 --> 20:56.329
I'm guessing they won't find
any bodies buried up there.

20:56.429 --> 20:57.394
O'shea won't be put off.

20:57.495 --> 21:00.758
You want him to fail.

21:00.858 --> 21:04.755
I don't want any blowback
on the department.

21:04.855 --> 21:07.519
Security is tight
as a presidential motorcade,

21:07.552 --> 21:09.383
and I'm making you
waits' chaperone.

21:09.518 --> 21:11.281
It's Johnson
and Moore's case.

21:11.381 --> 21:13.213
Not the bones on the hill.
They're yours.

21:13.313 --> 21:15.512
So I want you in charge

21:15.545 --> 21:17.276
of this fishing expedition,
detective.

21:17.376 --> 21:19.708
In case
anything goes wrong.

21:21.507 --> 21:23.505
I suspect your instincts
are right

21:23.605 --> 21:25.768
and this is just a scam
on waits' part.

21:25.868 --> 21:28.365
It'd be a disaster
for the department

21:28.500 --> 21:30.331
were o'shea
to be elected mayor.

21:30.498 --> 21:32.129
And for you.

21:35.326 --> 21:37.492
I'm a native son
of south central, bosch.

21:37.592 --> 21:40.489
I would hate to have to go
somewhere else

21:40.589 --> 21:42.620
to become
a chief of police.

21:42.720 --> 21:44.318
Although that might make
some people happy.

21:44.486 --> 21:47.583
[ Chuckles ]
Not necessarily.

21:47.682 --> 21:49.880
The devil you know...

21:53.976 --> 21:56.840
*

22:15.922 --> 22:16.921
hey.

22:17.021 --> 22:17.954
Hi.

22:19.219 --> 22:20.453
You're surprised.

22:20.518 --> 22:22.116
A little.
You're out of uniform.

22:22.216 --> 22:24.214
[ Chuckles ] You forgot.

22:24.314 --> 22:25.448
A little.

22:25.548 --> 22:27.012
You said
you were gonna call.

22:27.112 --> 22:28.445
[ Sighs ]

22:28.545 --> 22:30.709
Just hung up
with this assignment.

22:30.809 --> 22:33.441
Everything kind of
went out the window.

22:33.540 --> 22:35.005
What's the assignment?

22:35.104 --> 22:36.270
Raynard waits,

22:36.438 --> 22:38.436
guy with the body
in his Van.

22:38.502 --> 22:40.267
We're taking him out
on a field trip tomorrow,

22:40.434 --> 22:41.666
see if he's full of shit.
Hmm.

22:43.597 --> 22:46.094
You gonna invite me in or make
me stand out here all night?

22:46.194 --> 22:47.960
Yeah. Come in.

22:48.060 --> 22:51.557
*

22:51.657 --> 22:54.554
this isn't jazz.
What are you playing?

22:54.654 --> 22:57.651
My daughter e-mailed me
a playlist.

22:57.751 --> 23:01.648
You want a drink?
We can go out on the deck.

23:01.747 --> 23:02.779
Later.

23:14.436 --> 23:16.701
[ Razor buzzing ]

23:19.231 --> 23:20.962
[ Buzzing stops ]

23:21.062 --> 23:22.396
You're learning.

23:22.462 --> 23:23.960
That's right.

23:24.060 --> 23:26.058
I even got my own car.

23:26.157 --> 23:27.391
That's how you do it.

23:27.457 --> 23:29.522
You want I start a pot
of coffee?

23:29.622 --> 23:32.219
I got to go,
but I can put it on for you.

23:32.387 --> 23:33.851
No, I'm good.

23:36.383 --> 23:38.014
I hope you're not
too worn out.

23:38.114 --> 23:39.380
[ Chuckles ]

23:39.446 --> 23:41.244
I know you got
a big day today.

23:41.378 --> 23:43.409
Wish I could go with you.

23:43.509 --> 23:45.375
Any chance of getting me
on that detail?

23:45.474 --> 23:47.205
Assignment's already made.

23:47.373 --> 23:48.372
But thanks.

23:48.405 --> 23:50.070
You don't think I'm ready.

23:50.169 --> 23:52.201
It's not that.
We got it covered.

23:52.368 --> 23:54.998
It's all officers with a lot
of time on the job.

23:55.098 --> 23:56.264
No salty boots.

23:56.365 --> 23:58.895
You'll have your day
in the sun.

23:58.995 --> 24:01.026
When?

24:01.125 --> 24:02.359
Chomping at the bit.

24:02.392 --> 24:04.789
Always.

24:04.889 --> 24:06.521
[ Buzzer ]

24:06.621 --> 24:08.918
Man: Chow time, chow time,
chow time.

24:09.018 --> 24:11.384
All inmates, assemble
in front of your bunks.

24:11.484 --> 24:14.414
No talking
and tuck your shirts in.

24:14.514 --> 24:16.546
Attention in the compound,

24:16.646 --> 24:20.842
inmate Garcia -- last 3-1-0-8,
come to kitchen.

24:20.941 --> 24:23.139
[ Phone ringing ]

24:23.239 --> 24:25.071
I like your suit, crate.

24:25.170 --> 24:27.336
It's a nice cut on you.

24:27.402 --> 24:29.067
Oh, yeah.
Thanks.

24:29.167 --> 24:30.333
The wife said
she was tired

24:30.433 --> 24:32.164
of me looking like
a used car salesman.

24:32.332 --> 24:35.761
Sent me one of those guys
from Hong Kong,

24:35.861 --> 24:37.759
flies into the states
for a few days,

24:37.859 --> 24:40.157
works out of a hotel room
near l.A.X.

24:40.324 --> 24:42.788
[ Buzzer ]
Yep. I got the pinstripe.

24:42.887 --> 24:44.586
It's a little hot.

24:44.686 --> 24:46.518
But it makes me look slender,
right?

24:46.618 --> 24:48.649
You're about to blow away.
[ Chuckles ]

24:52.446 --> 24:55.376
You're good
to rock 'n' roll.

24:57.174 --> 24:58.540
Man:
All yours, detective.

24:58.640 --> 25:01.937
Officer, take ahold of him,
put him in the Van.

25:18.289 --> 25:19.987
Where's your attorney?

25:20.087 --> 25:24.284
I fired her.
I'm representing myself.

25:24.384 --> 25:26.282
Pull any shit,
I'll flip your "off" switch.

25:26.348 --> 25:28.046
You got it?

25:28.146 --> 25:29.279
Got it.

25:29.345 --> 25:30.977
Good.
Load him up.

25:37.405 --> 25:39.403
Not too late to stop
this side show.

25:39.503 --> 25:41.301
What are you afraid of,
bosch?

25:41.401 --> 25:42.999
Let's go solve some murders,
detective.

25:43.099 --> 25:44.698
Make some headlines?

25:44.798 --> 25:46.364
A video record is essential
to this inquiry.

25:46.463 --> 25:47.828
We find any kill sites
or graves,

25:47.928 --> 25:49.160
we're gonna need one.

25:49.261 --> 25:50.560
Sir, this is just
another photo op,

25:50.659 --> 25:51.958
and I'm on the record
with you here and now --

25:52.058 --> 25:52.923
I don't like it.

25:53.023 --> 25:54.089
Duly noted.

25:54.256 --> 25:55.421
Now let's go.

25:55.521 --> 25:58.386
Our initial stop
is in east L.A.

25:58.485 --> 26:00.650
Where waits killed
his first victim.

26:00.750 --> 26:02.581
That would be your case,
detective.

26:02.681 --> 26:04.580
I guarantee you
it never happened.

26:04.679 --> 26:07.144
Yeah, that remains to be seen,
doesn't it?

26:07.245 --> 26:08.543
Bosch:
I'm in the Van with waits.

26:08.643 --> 26:10.507
Everybody on channel eight.

26:37.217 --> 26:38.815
Waits:
You ever notice,

26:38.915 --> 26:40.347
weather's always so nice

26:40.447 --> 26:42.012
around Christmas
and new year's?

26:42.112 --> 26:45.609
They say when people back east
see the rose parade on TV,

26:45.709 --> 26:48.307
they pack their bags
for California.

26:48.407 --> 26:51.237
Well, you grew up here.

26:51.337 --> 26:56.200
It's easy to take it
for granted, right?

26:56.233 --> 26:58.663
Sell your bullshit
somewhere else, waits.

26:58.763 --> 27:01.395
Aww.
That's not polite.

27:01.494 --> 27:04.292
I'm sorry you're skeptical,
detective.

27:04.392 --> 27:06.755
I'm telling the truth.

27:08.222 --> 27:09.986
You know, I read about you,
detective.

27:10.086 --> 27:12.285
Up from such sad beginnings,

27:12.385 --> 27:15.881
from that place
where they put you after...

27:15.981 --> 27:17.280
Your mother was taken.

27:17.380 --> 27:20.510
And now look at you,

27:20.610 --> 27:23.540
a man on a mission.

27:23.640 --> 27:26.272
Isn't that what they say
about you?

27:26.372 --> 27:29.968
Or what you say
about yourself?

27:30.068 --> 27:31.999
No family.

27:32.167 --> 27:33.997
No life.

27:34.165 --> 27:36.163
Only cases.

27:36.196 --> 27:40.459
Only...The mission.

27:42.756 --> 27:47.752
You sit at home at night,
every night, all alone,

27:47.852 --> 27:53.147
surrounded by files and photos
of dead people.

27:53.247 --> 27:55.278
So, talk about
this first stop, waits,

27:55.378 --> 27:58.309
where you supposedly killed
Arthur delacroix 20 years ago.

27:58.408 --> 28:01.005
Actually, it was much easier
than you think,

28:01.140 --> 28:02.472
getting the boy into the Van.

28:02.571 --> 28:05.402
I was cruising the boulevard
one night.

28:05.502 --> 28:08.666
There he was
with his little backpack.

28:10.631 --> 28:13.461
He was standing there
so forlorn,

28:13.561 --> 28:16.958
like he didn't have a friend
in the world.

28:17.125 --> 28:18.889
I pulled over.

28:18.989 --> 28:21.188
I didn't really think
about it.

28:21.287 --> 28:23.719
I just pulled over.

28:23.819 --> 28:26.016
Rolled down the window.

28:26.117 --> 28:29.813
Said, "hi.

28:29.913 --> 28:32.444
Want to go to the movies?"

28:35.008 --> 28:37.407
He wanted to.

29:09.111 --> 29:11.242
Ahead, you see the bridge.

29:11.341 --> 29:13.473
Under the bridge,
that's where he died.

29:13.573 --> 29:15.338
We're going off-road here.
Left under the bridge.

29:15.438 --> 29:17.103
Our first location is ahead.

29:17.203 --> 29:20.068
Yeah.
Under the bridge.

29:20.134 --> 29:22.398
[ Police radio chatter ]

29:38.850 --> 29:42.180
Here.
We stop here.

29:51.904 --> 29:54.136
It's so empty.

29:54.236 --> 29:56.334
It's changed so much.

29:56.434 --> 30:01.729
You think of all the people
who used to work here,

30:01.829 --> 30:03.727
all gone.

30:03.827 --> 30:04.993
How would you know?

30:05.092 --> 30:06.391
My father worked here.

30:06.491 --> 30:08.955
They said
that's why he got sick.

30:09.056 --> 30:12.685
Asbestos and fiberglass
got in his lungs.

30:12.785 --> 30:17.580
Anyway, he died.

30:17.680 --> 30:19.513
And that was that.

30:19.612 --> 30:22.044
Too bad.

30:22.144 --> 30:24.042
We're going in there,
waits.

30:24.142 --> 30:26.672
Remember what we talked
about before.

30:26.772 --> 30:28.305
I know.

30:29.936 --> 30:31.368
You'll put me in the trunk,

30:31.468 --> 30:33.966
and I'll never see
the light of day again.

30:34.066 --> 30:35.431
[ Car door closes ]

30:42.325 --> 30:44.689
Okay.
Everybody, listen up.

30:44.789 --> 30:46.787
All right.

30:46.887 --> 30:48.319
We're all aware of
the security risk here.

30:48.419 --> 30:52.283
Mr. waits is gonna direct us
to the crime scenes,

30:52.383 --> 30:55.113
and we will be on top
of his every move.

30:55.213 --> 30:57.411
If and when we find
crime scenes,

30:57.511 --> 30:59.676
we pull waits out
and call in the coroner.

30:59.775 --> 31:02.107
Any questions?

31:02.207 --> 31:04.405
Okay.
Let's bring him out.

31:49.330 --> 31:52.627
Waits: Emergency power,
back there on the wall.

31:52.727 --> 31:54.492
Crate, check it.

31:54.591 --> 31:56.224
Got it.

32:02.418 --> 32:03.783
Where to?

32:03.917 --> 32:05.781
That way,
through there.

32:05.916 --> 32:07.180
There's stairs down
to the underneath.

32:07.280 --> 32:09.378
So, that's where
you took him?

32:09.478 --> 32:11.543
That's where I took them all,
down there.

32:11.643 --> 32:12.575
Jerry, clear it.

32:22.699 --> 32:24.199
Clear!

32:24.298 --> 32:25.330
Let's go.

32:52.339 --> 32:55.769
Come on. Keep moving.
Where are these stairs?

32:55.870 --> 32:57.401
Just through there,
detective.

32:57.501 --> 32:59.033
We're almost there.

32:59.133 --> 33:01.330
I can't wait to show you.

33:04.761 --> 33:05.693
Oh, shit.

33:05.861 --> 33:07.859
Stand him up.

33:07.892 --> 33:09.457
[ Grunting ]

33:09.557 --> 33:12.088
Up!
Ah, Jesus Christ.

33:12.187 --> 33:15.185
He's all right.
He's just got a bloody nose.
I think it's broken.

33:15.285 --> 33:17.649
Barrel, go get that first aid
kit out of the Van.

33:17.749 --> 33:18.849
Johnson: Yeah, sure.
You got it.

33:18.882 --> 33:19.848
Maybe we should
loosen his shackles.

33:19.948 --> 33:21.112
We don't need
a lawsuit here.

33:21.212 --> 33:23.177
No fucking way.
Bosch, just do it.

33:23.277 --> 33:24.708
We need to get down
steps to the basement.

33:24.843 --> 33:25.708
We got security covered.

33:25.842 --> 33:27.241
This is a bad idea.

33:27.340 --> 33:28.505
You're overruled.

33:28.605 --> 33:30.104
Now loosen his hands.

33:30.204 --> 33:32.069
If he trips again, he needs
to be able to break his fall.

33:32.169 --> 33:33.301
Are you
fucking kidding me?

33:33.401 --> 33:35.000
Just do it, detective!

33:36.232 --> 33:38.131
Jesus Christ.

33:56.280 --> 33:57.946
Hold him still.

33:58.046 --> 34:00.011
We get down
in the basement,

34:00.111 --> 34:02.209
you're going back
on the fucking chain.

34:02.308 --> 34:03.840
You got me?

34:15.462 --> 34:16.928
[ Object thuds ]

34:17.028 --> 34:19.625
Hey.
This thing works.

34:19.793 --> 34:23.189
Okay. So, we take
the elevator down.

34:23.289 --> 34:24.421
Crate, put him back
on the chain.

34:24.521 --> 34:27.785
All right.

34:27.851 --> 34:30.283
Give me your hands.
What if I fall again?

34:30.383 --> 34:32.181
Then you break your nose again,
so watch your step.

34:32.281 --> 34:34.879
Get your hands up.

34:36.910 --> 34:40.506
Waits, when was the last time
you were here?

34:40.606 --> 34:42.504
Not too long ago.

34:42.604 --> 34:43.670
Oh, shit!

34:43.771 --> 34:46.201
[ Gunshots ]

34:53.427 --> 34:57.024
Harry, don't!

34:59.621 --> 35:00.788
[ Door closes ]

35:21.869 --> 35:25.732
Officer needs help.
Shots fired. Officer down.

35:25.798 --> 35:28.763
Get me an r.A. Unit now!

35:55.805 --> 35:57.803
I got one dead
and one wounded officer --

35:57.903 --> 36:00.933
deputy d.A. Escobar,
detective Robert Moore.

36:01.033 --> 36:02.764
My partner
is in foot pursuit,

36:02.864 --> 36:04.762
and his direction of travel
is unknown.

36:04.862 --> 36:07.227
[ Groaning ]
It's okay.

36:07.327 --> 36:08.726
Have all units stay

36:08.826 --> 36:10.124
within a two-block radius
of my location.

36:10.224 --> 36:11.390
Hang in there, buddy.

36:11.490 --> 36:13.754
What's the eta
of the r.A. Unit?

36:13.854 --> 36:16.219
We're in the L.A. river
on sixth street.

36:16.318 --> 36:18.483
6w22 be advised.

36:18.583 --> 36:21.114
We have a 187 suspect
fleeing on foot.

36:21.214 --> 36:23.245
White male,
blue L.A. county jumpsuit.

36:23.345 --> 36:24.744
We need an airship now!

36:38.531 --> 36:41.962
[ Gunshots ]

37:00.245 --> 37:01.744
[ Panting ]

38:49.445 --> 38:52.043
[ Train whistle blows ]

39:20.750 --> 39:24.079
Hey!
Hey, I need your truck.

39:24.179 --> 39:25.278
Police business.

39:25.378 --> 39:27.843
Out now.
Keep 'er running.

39:29.708 --> 39:31.939
You're not police.

39:32.039 --> 39:34.304
No shit.

39:34.403 --> 39:35.603
[ Voice breaking ]
Por favor.

39:38.300 --> 39:39.299
Man: All right.
You're good.

39:39.399 --> 39:40.964
Come on through.

39:45.993 --> 39:47.858
[ Siren wails ]

39:47.957 --> 39:49.023
How's crate?

39:49.123 --> 39:50.722
He's breathing.

39:50.822 --> 39:53.020
They're taking him
to county.

39:53.119 --> 39:56.217
O'shea?

39:56.316 --> 39:59.081
First cockroach
out of dodge.

40:02.578 --> 40:04.876
Did you get it?
Tell me you got it.

40:04.976 --> 40:06.641
I got it, yeah,
but he took the card.

40:06.740 --> 40:08.006
Who took the card?
O'shea.

40:08.106 --> 40:09.705
Son of a bitch.

40:09.804 --> 40:11.603
There's the cloud,
you know?

40:11.703 --> 40:12.934
What do you mean,
the cloud?

40:13.034 --> 40:14.267
The backup to the cloud.

40:14.367 --> 40:15.732
If you have a drive,
I'll dub you a copy.

40:15.832 --> 40:17.465
Fuck o'shea. Did you see
what he did back there?

40:17.565 --> 40:18.996
I don't have a drive.

40:19.096 --> 40:20.062
I do.

40:24.858 --> 40:28.555
Make me a copy,
then erase it from the cloud.

40:33.382 --> 40:34.649
[ Sighs ]

40:34.749 --> 40:37.312
I gave you one directive,
bosch. One.

40:37.413 --> 40:38.711
Yeah, you did.
You were to see

40:38.811 --> 40:40.709
that waits and
this operation were secure.

40:40.809 --> 40:42.174
And what did you do?
You shit the bed.

40:42.274 --> 40:43.773
You got what you wanted.

40:43.873 --> 40:45.338
O'shea's prospects for mayor
are in the shitter.

40:45.439 --> 40:46.937
He'll be lucky
to keep his job as d.A.

40:47.037 --> 40:48.702
Waits was officially
in your custody, detective.

40:48.802 --> 40:50.567
So, technically, you,
not o'shea, lost waits.

40:50.667 --> 40:52.466
And you can be sure that's
how he will spin it.

40:52.565 --> 40:54.130
Do you have any idea
what kind of position

40:54.230 --> 40:55.463
that puts
this department in?

40:55.563 --> 40:57.194
My guy got shot up
behind this bullshit.

40:57.293 --> 40:58.627
This whole
situation's fugazi.

40:58.727 --> 41:00.957
Fugazi.

41:01.057 --> 41:03.423
Exactly.

41:03.489 --> 41:06.785
And now we have to un-fuck it,
don't we, detective?

42:06.997 --> 42:09.062
[ Indistinct conversations ]

42:09.162 --> 42:10.926
[ Helicopter blades whirring ]

42:13.058 --> 42:14.190
Detective bosch,
care to comment?

42:14.358 --> 42:17.720
[ Camera shutters clicking ]

42:25.348 --> 42:26.347
How's he doing?

42:26.446 --> 42:28.177
Prepping him for surgery.

42:28.345 --> 42:29.609
Is he gonna make it?

42:29.709 --> 42:30.575
Fingers crossed.

42:30.675 --> 42:32.840
What went wrong
out there?

42:32.940 --> 42:33.972
Everything.

42:42.597 --> 42:44.862
[ Monitor beeping,
respirator hissing ]

42:55.219 --> 42:58.317
You're gonna be all right,
brother.

43:01.847 --> 43:03.413
[ Straining ]

43:18.798 --> 43:22.894
Don't worry.
I'm gonna get it back for you.

43:44.041 --> 43:45.673
Waits got his badge, too.

43:45.773 --> 43:47.937
Oh, shit.

43:48.037 --> 43:50.270
Shit. Shit.

43:50.336 --> 43:51.601
This is bad.

43:51.701 --> 43:53.899
Could've been me.
What do you mean?

43:53.998 --> 43:55.398
I handed waits off
to crate,

43:55.498 --> 43:56.963
told him to re-cuff him
to the chain.

43:57.063 --> 43:58.095
Waits made his move then.

43:58.262 --> 43:59.594
[ Sighs ]

44:10.617 --> 44:12.315
Harry.

44:13.980 --> 44:14.912
You okay?

44:15.012 --> 44:16.379
Yeah, I'm fine.

44:16.478 --> 44:18.876
Crate's in bad shape.

44:18.976 --> 44:20.242
They're asking for blood.

44:20.275 --> 44:21.706
That's never good.

44:21.806 --> 44:23.938
See you later, okay?

44:24.038 --> 44:25.037
Where you going?

44:25.137 --> 44:26.736
Back to division,

44:26.835 --> 44:29.633
help out with the phones in case
somebody dimes waits off.

44:29.733 --> 44:31.831
Because I'm gonna be there
when we find him.

44:43.221 --> 44:44.353
[ Spits ]

44:48.549 --> 44:50.347
[ Grunts ]

45:00.671 --> 45:01.836
Come on!

45:03.535 --> 45:04.567
[ Grunts ]

45:13.059 --> 45:14.226
[ Chuckles ]

45:18.222 --> 45:21.751
[ Humming ]
